    <section id="vowels" class="vowels-section">
        <h2 class="section-title"><mark>About Vowels</h2>

        <p class="about-text">
            There's total 21 vowels in Korean and we can divide vowels by single vowels and double vowels.
        </p>
        <b>Single vowels and double vowels</b>
        <p>Single vowels : "„Öè „Öê „Öì „Öî „Öó „Öö „Öú „Öü „Ö° „Ö£"<br> Dobule vowels : "„Öë „Öï „Öõ „Ö† „Öí „Öñ „Öò „Öù „Öô „Öû „Ö¢" </p>
        <p>Single vowels can be dived by various factors.</p>
        <table border='1'>
            <tr>
                <td rowspan='2'></td>
                <td colspan='2'>Vowel </td>
                <td colspan='2'> lower vowel </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Flat vowels</td>
                <td>Round vowels</td>
                <td>Flat vowels</td>
                <td>Round vowels</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td> High vowels </td>
                <td>„Ö£(i)</td>
                <td>„Öü(√º)</td>
                <td>„Ö°(…®)</td>
                <td>„Öú(u)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Middle vowels</td>
                <td>„Öî(e)</td>
                <td>„Öö(√∂)</td>
                <td>„Öì( å)</td>
                <td>„Öó(o)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td> Lower vowels</td>
                <td>„Öê(…õ)</td>
